To automate the selection of a panel like a an automated slider/image gallery you will need to fake clicking on each tab (pill) link.

The basics are:

- Add something to the markup that signifies that this is a _&quot;tab slider.&quot;_ In this case, a `data-` attribute.
- Loop the collection and instantiate each tab slider. For each tab slider:
  - Get a reference to each tab.
  - Count the tabs - for use with Modulo operator (`%1`) and incrementor variable to determine which panel to display.
  - Create a function that can get called repeatedly, `setTimeout`, that will advance to the next panel by triggering a click event on a tab.

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    $( &#39;[data-widget=&quot;tab-slider&quot;]&#39; ).each( function ( i, el ) {

      const $container   = $( this );
      const $sliderLinks = $container.find( &#39;.nav-link&#39; );
      const panelCount   = $sliderLinks.length;
      const delay        = 3000; // milleseconds
      let   index        = 0;

      function nextTabSliderPanel() {

        $sliderLinks.eq( index++ % panelCount ).trigger( &#39;click&#39; );
        setTimeout( nextTabSliderPanel, delay );

      }
      
      nextTabSliderPanel(); // Start the slider.

    } );

